From: Heiko Gleu <heiko_gleu@web.de>
Subject: [PATCH] OSPRay superbuild: forward CMAKE_POLICY_VERSION_MINIMUM=3.5 to subprojects

CMake 4.0 (shipped with Ubuntu 26.04 as `cmake` 4.2.x) removes
compatibility with `cmake_minimum_required(VERSION < 3.5)`. Several
upstream subprojects pulled in by the OSPRay superbuild still declare
ancient minimums (OpenVKL, OpenPGL, glfw, etc.):

    CMake Error at CMakeLists.txt:6 (cmake_minimum_required):
      Compatibility with CMake < 3.5 has been removed from CMake.

CMake offers an opt-out via `-DCMAKE_POLICY_VERSION_MINIMUM=3.5`, but
this must be passed explicitly to each ExternalProject. Setting it on
the top-level superbuild configure does NOT propagate.

This patch adds the flag to every subproject CMAKE_ARGS list, right
after `-DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=${CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH}`.

Apply to: <ospray-source>/scripts/superbuild/dependencies/dep_*.cmake
       and <ospray-source>/scripts/superbuild/build_ospray.cmake

---
Example (dep_openvkl.cmake), apply analogously to all dep_*.cmake +
build_ospray.cmake:

diff --git a/scripts/superbuild/dependencies/dep_openvkl.cmake b/scripts/superbuild/dependencies/dep_openvkl.cmake
--- a/scripts/superbuild/dependencies/dep_openvkl.cmake
+++ b/scripts/superbuild/dependencies/dep_openvkl.cmake
@@ -36,6 +36,7 @@
     CMAKE_ARGS
       -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=${CMAKE_PREFIX_PATH}
+      -DCMAKE_POLICY_VERSION_MINIMUM=3.5
       -DCMAKE_CXX_COMPILER=${CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER}
       -DCMAKE_C_COMPILER=${CMAKE_C_COMPILER}
       -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=${CMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE}
